    <p>Consider it like this: If cross-device tracking is gathering the puzzle pieces of a customer's behavior, cross-device attribution is what puts those pieces together into something that genuinely resembles what happened and influenced the sale. This difference is important because attribution directly influences how you spend marketing dollars and gauge the effectiveness of your campaigns.</p>
    
